Sentence.Value: A highway connects two cities.
The distance between the cities is the length of highway.
Highway is constructed by a contractor.
A tender has tender number, amount and details of the project.
Highway has construction cost and toll price.
Toll booths have an address along with a unique ID.
Every toll booth has toll associated for every type of vehicle.
Toll booth is managed by a manager.
A toll booth has a lane count.
Surveillance footage of the toll booth is provided to a surveillance agency.
Tender have a start date and end date.
Projects not finishing before the end date are penalized.
An engineer looks after a project.
Every highway has a unique number identifying it.
A student can enrol for a course.
To take a course, there are prerequisites that need to be satisfied.
Course has prerequisites to satisfy.
A student will have general registration number, division, roll number, admission year, current subjects.
Student's contact information like address, mobile number will be stored.
A student will also have a library card.
A student can take at most 3 books from the library.
Books currently owned by the student is tracked.
There are many communities in the university.
A student can register to some community.
Every community has a group of students as administrator.
Communities host events throughout the year.
Number of people attended, cost of session, speaker and title of the event are stored.
A course has a code, title and duration.
Syllabus of the course consists of five units.
Every unit comprises 8 hours of class room section.
Every unit has 1 hours self-study section.
A course has upper limit for total number of students.
There are faculties which can teach that course.
Every time slot will be associated with a faculty.
Two faculties at the most can teach any course.
Time table for the course contains which topic will be taught on what date.
There is homework associated with every lecture.
Lecture homework have hard deadline and soft deadline.
There are marks which are awarded when homework is submitted within a deadline.
A course also has a lecture room associated with it.
A teacher has a name, phone number, email address and postal address as his personal information.
A teacher can teach one or more courses.
Teacher have a field of expertise.
Teacher take guide one to five projects at a time.
Teacher can get involved in projects requiring research.
Research can be sponsored or non-sponsored.
Teacher can have list of publications.
Students can take projects.
A project is taken by two to five students.
Every project has a faculty as guide.
Every project has a title, domain, team members and guide.
There is team leader for a project.
Project starts at a date and has 6 months to complete.
Project expires in 6 month after starting.
A college is divided into departments.
Every department has name and location.
Every department has a HOD from its faculties.
Departments are further divided into divisions.
Divisions are further divided into batches.
A batch can have 10 to 20 students.
A division can have 40 to 60 students.
Every department has its maximum capacity.
Number of students cannot exceed the maximum capacity of the departments.
A subject has an examination.
Completion of a course awards credits.
There are other universities associated with us.
An airport can be international or domestic.
Manager looks after an airport.
Airport have specific number of runways.
Every runway has a code.
Airplanes have a number, seating capacity and other information.
There are many airline companies.
Every company owns some airplanes.
Every company has a country associated with it.
Airports have certain number of hangers.
Planes can be commercial or private jets.
Buses go to various places.
Buses ply on various route.
Every route has a frequency.
A bus can either be regular, semi luxury or AC Volvo.
Buses have plate number.
Different types of buses ply on different route.
Buses ply between bus stations.
Buses also go to selected places out of the state.
Non stationary staff include driver and conductor.
Non stationary staff which are away from home are provided dormitories to stay.
Every district station has dormitories.
Stationary staff include station management and other people.
Stations can be small village station, district station, division stations.
District station have many village stations.
Division Stations have many district stations under them.
A special type of division station is called headquarters.
Headquarters manages all the stations, buses and routes.
Every route has list of stops.
List of stops for different busses are different.
Stops covered by AC Volvo are covered but regular bus but the reverse is not true.
Tickets can be booked only from division or district stations.
Online booking of ticket is not available.
Tickets contain ticket number, amount, route, destination, source, and passenger details.
Passenger detail include number of adults and number of children.
Ticket amount is different for adult and children for same route.
Route passes are available for selected routes.
Route passes have a cost associated with them.
A traveller can have many route passes.
Regular busses can have standees.
Records are maintained of number of traveller for particular route on particular day.
Some district stations have repair stations.
Cargo hubs are present at all district stations.
Every station has a capacity for the number of buses that can be parked.
A visitor can register to become registered user.
Customers are awarded with points on shopping.
All products are assigned shopping points.
Product has a category, a subcategory, and a price.
There are images and reviews of products.
Every product belongs to one or more category.
Products are identified by a number.
Log for every registered customers is to be maintained.
Every bill comprises items bought, date, bill number and amount of the bill.
Log should contain details like date, bill number and bill amount.
Some of the products are not replaceable.
Delivery store has a coverage area.
Delivery stores are owned privately by a person.
Delivery vehicle can be a bike, or a truck.
A user can be registered by creating new account
Up votes to question or answer gives reputation to a user.
User has privileges based on reputation.
Any user can ask or answer a question
Questions have a view count.
A user can have favourite question or answer
A user has list of up/down votes questions
A user has list of questions asked or answered
All the reputation of user is stored as his log
Questions award bounty to the user answering them.
Questions can be either protected, closed or open.
A user can comment or answer a question.
Comments can also have up votes
Questions have tags and categories under which the question falls
A user can have his favourite tags
A question can have zero or more answers.
Only one answer as accepted answer for a question.
Doctors have a name, an address and a degree.
Patients go to doctor for check-up.
A doctor can check many patients.
Doctor has timing in which he is available.
All the staff belong to one of the 3 shifts.
Doctor can be specialist or a general physician.
Specialist can have a speciality domain.
Every doctor is allotted a cabin.
Patients visit the doctor with symptoms.
Patients are diagnosed by doctors.
Patients have to take appointment.
Appointment consists of name of patient, PIN and timing.
Every patient is assigned to a doctor.
Patients have previous clinical history.
Doctors have timings to attend OPD.
There are different departments in the hospital.
A specialists have a department.
Nurses are assigned to patients.
Nurses are also assigned to doctors.
There are different types of rooms in the hospital.
Rooms can be ICU, OT, general ward or private suite.
Reports are managed by administrators.
Reports are uploaded by doctors.
Reports have a patient index number and doctor index number.
Medicines have a name and official name and content.
Medicines have a manufacturer and distributor.
Medicine have a date of manufacturing and expiry date.
Medicines can be categorised as categoryx and categoryy.
A hospital can have various wings like patient wings, doctors dormitory, cancer cure centre.
Hospital wings have capacity.
Ambulance have a plate number, instruments list and GPS device Id.
Movement of ambulance is tracked.
Every wing has instruments and cost of each instrument along with model number, manufacturer and other such details.
Banking can be personal or commercial.
All the customers can be divided in above 2 categories.
A person can open a saving account or current account
A person can deposit, withdraw money from saving account.
An account has an interest rate.
Junior account is for a person lesser than 18 years of age.
A person with account may ask for services like debit card, online banking and mobile banking.
Log book for every customer is maintained.
Log book contain amount of transaction, transaction via, credit/debit.
Banks have branches and ATMs.
ATM have address, number and other information.
ATM maintain log book, containing all the transaction for that ATM.
ATMs also have 2 or more CCTV camera which provide video footage.
Every ATM have a security guard.
Security guard has name, number and company.
There are selected companies from where bank hires security guards.
ATMs can have one or more machines depending on the demand.
Every machine has a model number, manufacturer and mac address.
Clerks deal with the customer.
A branch manager manages clerks.
Vaults have model number, manufacturer details and password.
Only branch manager knows the password of the vault in his branch.
Customers are given check books.
A check book has a leaf count and range of checks in it.
Company board regulates companies in a country.
There are many domains under which a company may function.
The person registering a company is the founder of the company.
Company may have a board of director or a managing director.
CEO's, CFO's and CTO's work under a director.
A company can have a director or a president.
There are rules and regulations of the board.
Rules are divided under sections and subsections.
Every rule has a unique number that identifies that rule.
List of stake holder contains start date and end date and share of the person in that period.
Car can be wagon, sedan or SUV.
A company can have many factories
A factory has a location and manager.
A factory has one or many assembly lines.
The chief engineer looks after a factory.
Cars is made up from chassis, engine, transmission and tyres.
Engine is identified by an engine number.
Every engine carries an engine number.
Engine has capacity and power generated.
Engine has cylinders and pistons.
All cars have a manufacturing date.
Every part in the car has an id.
Every account has a domain name, user name and password.
Every mail has a sender, receiver, subject, attachment and body.
There can be one more recipients for a mail.
